\cf0 - some error situations in Debug will send you back to Edit mode without your requesting it.\
\
- commands in Debug which also match a 6502 mnemonic won't work, you need to put a space in between command and parameter, e. g. LDA10 or DEC won't work but L DA10 and D EC will.\
\
- extremely annoyingly, you must use BRK to return to the debugger.\'a0 A program using RTS will usually hang or crash.\
\
- if your program disables stage 2 Vblank the Break key won't work.\'a0 Probably because the Rev. A OS didn't have a Break key vector, it was added later.\'a0 So the Assembler Editor cartridge had to use a workaround which has deficiencies.\
\
- zero page labels will generate a 2-byte address when used with instructions that also have absolute mode, e. g. LDA RTCLOCK+2 where RTCLOCK = $12\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
